{"headline": "Today's Research Reports on Stocks to Watch: Cisco Systems and Apple Inc. - MarketWatch", "author": null, "tick": "AAPL", "link": "https://www.marketwatch.com/story/todays-research-reports-on-stocks-to-watch-cisco-systems-and-apple-inc-2018-02-06", "text": "Published: Feb 06, 2018 (ACCESSWIRE via COMTEX) -- NEW YORK, NY / ACCESSWIRE / February 6, 2018 / Apple and Cisco both fell along with the market but the two companies had exciting news yesterday. The two have teamed up with two insurance companies to offer insurance policies to companies to protect them financially against cyber-attacks. RDI Initiates Coverage on: Cisco Systems, Inc.   Apple Inc.   Cisco Systems' shares closed down 5.25% yesterday on about 52.4 million shares traded. Cisco and Apple are teaming up with Aon and Allianz to offer a new cybersecurity package. As part of the package, Aon will perform security consulting and Allianz will provide cyber security insurance coverage at discounted rates for customers using apple devices and Cisco security products. It was last week that company revealed a study that found businesses with advanced security setups are still seeing several weeks of sales delays and losing hundreds in millions of dollars in revenue. While the two companies are not the ones directly selling insurance, Cisco CEO Chuck Robbins said that the move is a part of the company's new \"holistic\" risk management efforts. Access RDI's Cisco Systems, Inc. Research Report at:   Apple's shares closed down 2.50% on Monday with nearly 73 million shares traded. One of the biggest headlines in the market yesterday was Cisco and Apple forming a partnership with two insurers to help companies against cyber-attacks. Apple CEO Tim Cook remarked, \"The choice of technology providers plays a critical role in any company's defense against cyber-attacks. That's why, from the beginning, Apple has built products from the ground up with security in mind, and one of the many reasons why businesses around the world are choosing our products to power their enterprise.\" In other exciting news, according to the Wall Street Journal, the tech giant's apple music could overtake Spotify in the number of paid subscribers in the United States. Access RDI's Apple Inc. Research Report at:   Our Actionable Research on Cisco Systems, Inc. and Apple Inc. can be downloaded free of charge at Research Driven Investing. Research Driven Investing We are committed to providing relevant and actionable information for the self-directed investor. Our research is reputed for being a leader in trusted, in-depth analysis vital for informed strategic trading decisions. The nimble investor can leverage our analysis and collective expertise to execute a disciplined approach to stock selection. RDInvesting has not been compensated; directly or indirectly; for producing or publishing this document. Disclaimer: This article is written by an independent contributor of RDInvesting.com and Nadia Noorani, a CFA\u00ae charter holder, has provided necessary guidance in preparing the document templates. RDInvesting.com is neither a registered broker dealer nor a registered investment advisor. For more information please read our full disclaimer at . CONTACT For any questions, inquiries, or comments reach out to us directly at: Address: Research Driven Investing, Unit #901 511 Avenue of the Americas, New York, NY, 10011 Email: contact@rdinvesting.com CFA\u00ae and Chartered Financial Analyst\u00ae are registered trademarks owned by CFA Institute. SOURCE: RDInvesting.com   Copyright 2018 ACCESSWIRE Copyright \u00a9 2018 MarketWatch, Inc.  All rights reserved. By using this site you agree to the , , and .", "source": "https://www.marketwatch.com/"}
