{"headline": "Global Connected Car Solutions Industry - MarketWatch", "author": null, "tick": "AAPL", "link": "https://www.marketwatch.com/story/global-connected-car-solutions-industry-2018-02-06", "text": "Published: NEW YORK, Fev. 6, 2018 /PRNewswire/ --\u00a0Read the full report:     The report provides separate comprehensive analytics for the US, Canada, Japan, Europe, Asia-Pacific, Latin America, and Rest of World.  Annual estimates and forecasts are provided for the period 2015 through 2024. Market data and analytics are derived from primary and secondary research. Company profiles are primarily based on public domain information including company URLs.    - Audi AG - Bayerische Motoren Werke AG - Daimler AG - Ford Motor Company - Fiat Chrysler Automobiles N.V. - General Motors Company    Read the full report:   CONNECTED CAR SOLUTIONS MCP-7009 A GLOBAL STRATEGIC BUSINESS REPORT CONTENTS     Study Reliability and Reporting Limitations Disclaimers Data Interpretation & Reporting Level Quantitative Techniques & Analytics Product Definitions and Scope of Study Embedded Connectivity Smartphone Connectivity Tethered Connectivity     1. INDUSTRY OVERVIEW Internet of Things: The Technology Platform for Connected Cars Table 1: With Over 300% Projected Growth in Connected Cars Penetration by 2025, the Automotive Industry Represents a Growing Segment in the IoT Ecosystem: % Breakdown of IoT Connected Devices (in Million) by Type the Years 2017, 2020 and 2025 (includes corresponding Graph/Chart) Connected Cars: The Future of Driving As Post Recession Recovery Growth in the Automotive Industry Slows Down, Disruptive Technologies Will Drive the Revenue Potential of the Industry Rethinking Revenue Streams: Auto OEMs Focus on Differentiated In-Vehicle Experience to Counterbalance Falling Revenues from Slowing New Car Sales Table 2: Automobile Industry's Migration Towards New Value Creation and Revenue Streams to Make \"Connectivity\" the Core Area of Future Growth and Focus: